%N A280432 Maximum size of a set whose integrity can be checked with n weighings.
%C A280432 This sequence arises in the following problem: Given a set of binary elements (e.g., coins that may have one of the two weights), determine whether all of them are the same by weighing equally sized non-overlapping subsets n times. a(n) is the maximum size of a set whose integrity can be checked with n weighings.
%C A280432 The next terms are probably a(7) = 2234 and a(8) = 9966 (from the Kozlov/Vu reference). - _Konstantin Knop_, Oct 18 2017
%C A280432 ((3^n-1)/2)*(n+1)*n^((n-1)/2) >= a(n) >= 2^((1/2)*n*log(n)-n*(2+o(1))) [Alon&Vu]. - _Andrey Zabolotskiy_, Oct 23 2017
